narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: IV methods, its application to gender wage gap, and MTE method LATE method and external validity (binary, continuous, and simulted instruments) Asymmetric information and its estimation (Auction and Asymmetric information)

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course's strength is that we can gain insights from several professors at only one class. The weakness is that unorganized feature of the class, and ambiguous class requirement.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I just suggest this class because of the department's requirement on the empirics paper. (I have a disagreeing opinion on this as well, but this is another story.) You may want to be selective on your effort to study each topic covered by three lecturers depending on your interest. All of them are on the frontier in their own way, so the contents were interesting themselves.
